    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix inconsistent num_tlvs handling in NR PNF config request pack/unpack functions\n\n### Summary\nThe NR PNF config request message handling contained inconsistencies between pack and unpack functions compared to the LTE implementation. The `num_tlvs` field was not properly handled in the NR version, causing potential message parsing issues during P5 interface communication.\n\nThe issue was that `pack_nr_pnf_config_request` had the `num_tlvs` push operation commented out, while `unpack_nr_pnf_config_request` was not pulling this field at all, despite the field being present in the NR structure definition.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p5.c`: \n  - Uncommented and enabled `push8(pNfapiMsg->num_tlvs, ppWritePackedMsg, end)` in `pack_nr_pnf_config_request`\n  - Added `pull8(ppReadPackedMsg, &pNfapiMsg->num_tlvs, end)` in `unpack_nr_pnf_config_request`\n  - Made NR implementation consistent with LTE implementation for `num_tlvs` field handling\n\n"
}